83
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:17,584
‐ <i>♪ In disorder ♪</i>

84
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:20,554
[singing in Japanese]

85
00:05:20,621 --> 00:05:22,656
‐ Jesus! She killed 'em all.

86
00:05:22,723 --> 00:05:26,026
What in the goddamn hell is she?

87
00:05:26,092 --> 00:05:27,427
‐ <i>♪ No need ruler ♪</i>

88
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,329
[singing in Japanese]

89
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:31,064
Man: Thought your shield
was bulletproof.

90
00:05:31,131 --> 00:05:33,600
‐ Couple slugs bounced
off the rocks and hit me.

91
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:35,636
Long as it's not my head,
I'm good.

92
00:05:35,702 --> 00:05:39,205
Man: I told you this was gonna
be dangerous. No one listens.

93
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:40,206
‐ Where's Pito?

94
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:41,474
Man #2: She's down there

95
00:05:41,542 --> 00:05:43,977
fartin' around
with the last two guys.

96
00:05:44,044 --> 00:05:45,345
‐ [grumbles]

97
00:05:45,411 --> 00:05:47,380
‐ <i>♪ Raise your flag ♪</i>

98
00:05:47,447 --> 00:05:48,649
‐ [singing in Japanese]

99
00:05:48,715 --> 00:05:49,650
‐ <i>♪ White or black... ♪</i>

100
00:05:49,716 --> 00:05:51,251
‐ Get it over with already.

101
00:05:51,317 --> 00:05:52,452
‐ I'd like to.

102
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:57,023
He still has his gun, though,

103
00:05:57,090 --> 00:06:00,561
so I'm just standing here,
waiting for him to draw it.

104
00:06:00,627 --> 00:06:03,296
It's not right to shoot
a defenseless person.

105
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,098
I couldn't live with myself
if I did.

106
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:08,969
‐ But you don't have a problem
watching that poor guy suffer.

107
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:11,905
We don't have time for this.
Do him already.

108
00:06:11,972 --> 00:06:13,974
‐ Fine, whatever. There.

109
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:17,110
‐ Gah! [grunting]

110
00:06:17,177 --> 00:06:20,380
‐ Uh‐oh. He's still holding on.

111
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:21,715
‐ [grunts]

112
00:06:21,782 --> 00:06:23,984
‐ Oh, my God,
would you let go already?

113
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:27,187
‐ Is this fun for you,
torturing another player?

114
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:28,655
Psycho!

115
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:34,027
‐ Is it fun being on a team
of thirty ganging up on six?

116
00:06:34,094 --> 00:06:37,430
Hell, yes! It's hard
to pick which is more fun,

117
00:06:37,497 --> 00:06:39,332
and I know
that if we switched places,

118
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,667
you'd do the same to me, buddy.

119
00:06:40,734 --> 00:06:43,737
‐ Let go! This is
the one chance you got, man!

120
00:06:43,804 --> 00:06:45,338
Drop me, and kill that bitch!

121
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:48,174
‐ No way.
Until these guys are dead,

122
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,543
we're in this thing together.

123
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:51,612
Besides, our leaders
are listening in,

124
00:06:51,678 --> 00:06:53,814
and I bet they're
on their way to save us.

125
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,481
‐ Let me go.

126
00:06:55,549 --> 00:06:57,851
‐ Right. Back to it.

127
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,987
Why won't you die?

128
00:07:01,054 --> 00:07:03,590
[sighs] This is why
I hate using pistols.

129
00:07:03,657 --> 00:07:05,759
And now I'm out of ammo. Hmph.

130
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:07,961
‐ You had a solid strategy.

131
00:07:08,028 --> 00:07:11,097
You fought well,
but you have to face reality.

132
00:07:11,164 --> 00:07:12,432
Even if your leaders come,

133
00:07:12,498 --> 00:07:14,334
they don't stand
a chance against us.

134
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,569
‐ [growls]

135
00:07:15,636 --> 00:07:16,903
M: Tell 'em this.

136
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:18,805
Resign now, or else.

137
00:07:18,872 --> 00:07:21,107
‐ No, you idiot!
Where's the fun in that?!

138
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:23,944
New idea.
Tell your leaders this instead.

139
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:26,613
"We totally got our asses
kicked by those guys.

140
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,481
They were so tough,
but you're tougher,

141
00:07:28,549 --> 00:07:31,151
so please come on up,
and avenge us." Hee hee.

142
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:32,719
‐ Can you do that?
‐ Uh‐huh.

143
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:35,355
And when they find you,
they're gonna butcher you all.

144
00:07:35,421 --> 00:07:36,723
‐ You're all gonna pay for this!

145
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,191
‐ Look at your faces.

146
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:41,494
That's the kind of hate
I've been waiting for.

147
00:07:41,562 --> 00:07:42,495
Later, boys.

148
00:07:42,563 --> 00:07:44,397
[both stammer]

149
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:45,899
‐ You're all bastards!

150
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:47,467
‐ Rot in hell!

151
00:07:49,936 --> 00:07:52,372
[Pito chuckles]
Seemed like those two

152
00:07:52,438 --> 00:07:54,474
got to be good friends
at the end there.

153
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:58,512
In ten minutes, they'll be
buying drinks for each other.

154
00:07:58,579 --> 00:08:00,113
How cool is that?

155
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:04,350
‐ God damn it! What the hell
happened up there?!

156
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:06,219
‐ Every last one of 'em's dead.

157
00:08:06,286 --> 00:08:08,354
‐ I'll make 'em pay
for what they did to‐‐

158
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:09,656
‐ [screams]
‐ [leaders gasp]

159
00:08:21,935 --> 00:08:24,370
Pito: One more to go, and‐‐

160
00:08:24,437 --> 00:08:26,973
No. Wait. [groans]

161
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:31,845
Bummer.
I really wanted to kill him.

162
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,382
‐ Damn, dude.
How many did she kill?

163
00:08:36,449 --> 00:08:39,052
‐ I stopped counting
when she got to 20.

164
00:08:39,119 --> 00:08:42,455
‐ She went full‐on berserk.
She even used her hands, man.

165
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:47,427
‐ I know that gun.
It's an M107A1. There's, like,

166
00:08:47,493 --> 00:08:50,330
